cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the problem of segmenting drivable paths in urban environments using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of this segmentation for autonomous driving, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper uses weakly-supervised learning, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of semantic segmentation, which could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
